text: Tallapoosa County is a county in the U.S. state of Alabama. "ACES Tallapoosa County Office" (links/history), Alabama Cooperative Extension System (ACES), 2007, webpage: ACES-Tallapoosa. As of the 2020 census, the population was 41,311. The county seat is Dadeville. The name Tallapoosa is of Creek origin, and many Indian villages were along the banks of the lower river before the 19th century. Tallapoosa County was founded on December 18, 1832. == References == Category:1832 establishments in Alabama Category:Alabama counties
